JS if:

- Use the JavaScript if statement to execute a block of code when a condition is true.
- syntax:
            if (condition) {
                // code to execute if the condition is true
            }

- ⚠️ Note that if is in lowercase letters. Uppercase letters (If or IF) will generate a
    JavaScript error.
    
- eg: Make a "Good day" greeting if the hour is less than 18:00:
            
            if (new Date().getHours() < 18) {
                document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Good day!";
            }